content: This App is very nice, one of my top favorites!!!
replyContent: You are probably still using the Free version. Use the start icon with the + symbol to start the Paid version. After checking your notes in the Paid version you can remove the Free version from your device.

content: Pretty solid and straight forward. Really dig it. Would it be possible to get an optional description box for each note/list item? When I use a to do list (for example), I like to have my purpose or motivation for the task listed also, especially if it's something I've simply dumped on the list to do later. It's too easy to get emotionally detached from an item listed a couple months ago. It's nice to be able to attach a note to remind myself of why it was important to me.
replyContent: Thanks! Just turn your task into a folder. Then you can add as many task details as you want.

content: Brilliant! I've been looking for a focused task list that allows MULTIPLE sub-task levels/checklists. Can Group projects to locations or people. Can instantly take photos with any project or task. Assign any tasks to the Today list on demand without needing to create a new list. Incredibly easy to use yet powerful features.

I especially like the widget automated shortcut method to directly open a note related to any person, place, phone number, video -- ANY note without drilling down into the app. Also there is a user manual in the main menu. The developer has thought of everything. Good show. Hard to imagine any improvements.
its great

Thanks.It works.wonderfull app
replyContent: You are probably still using the Free version. Use the start icon with the + sign. After checking your notes in the Paid version you can remove the Free version from your device. Write an email to info@foranylist.com if you need further help.

content: This is by far the most aerodynamic and sophisticated task app that has ever been created! and trust me I have had them all. This is a GOD SEND! The HOLY GRAIL of life Organization. To the developers thank you thank you thank. TOTAL VICTORY! üèÜüèÜüèÜüèÜüèÜüèÜ
This app is changed my entire life. Thank you so much for your help.

I use this app on a daily basis. It's very functional with lots of extras. The developer is attentive to customer requests for ideas and app improvements. The wait is never long before he has an update available. I considered switching to an iPhone but I couldn't find a comparable app like (To-Do-List) so it was a no brainer to stay with an Android phone.

I downloaded the free version of this app and after 10 minutes, I purchased the pro version. It is a superbly useful tool which has many options and settings. You can create many different types of lists with different colours. You can even secure lists with your fingerprint. I could not find how to do this but an email to a very responsive dev provided me with the answer. A simple but effective way of securing your notes. This is a truly great app with a very supportive dev. Highly recommended.

My old list maker wouldn't transfer to new phone. I found this. Amazingly powerful and flexible, with database like functionality, all done with simple lists. I'm very visual, so the ability to color entries (and sort by color, among many other choices) was just what I was looking for. When I discovered how to link items to places or people items (again, so easily!) my world changed. Pro is worth every penny. GREAT app.
This app is awesome! The developers are quick to respond to your inquiries. An I installed it on a new device with my folders an was able to restore from my email!! They ROCK!!! Thx!!

I have been messing with this app to see if I like it. I am so glad I found this app. I went ahead and purchased it. I like that I can make ma y folders. There are many other features that I haven't used yet.
A must have for those who want a beautiful and simple yet feature-rich to-do, note-taking and reminder app. Love this app! üëçüèªüëçüèª

I used the free version and quickly found that I was willing to shell out for the full version; reasonably priced. Widget makes it quick and easy to open. I just need to quickly log carbs. I have diabetes and recent (bad) lab results motivated me to keep track in the simplest way, so this is perfect for me. I wanted this information seperate and carb log apps were too fiddly and overblown.
Finally organization that gets me. Simple yet very versatile. Customizable.

Wow! What a versatile app for lists! Just what I was looking for: Does checklists, shopping lists, itemized (numbered) lists (plus basic lists). And a great set of additional features: Sort, attach pics, set reminders & such, folders & sub-folders (unlimited in number & sub-levels in paid version), allows "locking" a list on the screen (great for shopping lists), etc... And each item in a list or folder can have a different colored font--some 10+ different colors. Polished appearance as well.
Great app -- nice approach! Very impressive appearance & performance....really worthy of 5 stars üòÄ
I love it.

Absolutely love this app! I would give that last star if you would make it so that the shopping list calculates the total as you shop. Add that and this app would be superior over any other app I've tried! Great job!!
replyContent: In the newest release you can view the total cost of checked products (in a locked shopping list). Thanks for your feedback.

content:
This app is great. Could you make the schedule with folders like tomorrow, 
this week, this month , etc. I dont want a long schedule list. Thank you.
replyContent: In the latest release a period bar has been added that allows you to quickly jump to the desired period. Thanks again for your feedback.

content:
This app would be great if, when I set a task to be daily, it actually 
showed up daily. If I check something, it just stays there until I delete 
it, and then I have to remake it again. That kinda defeats the purpose of 
this. It would be nice if a recurring note like that could be checked off, 
and then appear again for the next day. The rest of the app is okay, a 
little awkward, but I'll happily give this a better rating if that daily 
thing is fixed. Edit: Thank you so much to the developers for walking me 
thru my idiocy. Seriously though, I really do appreciate it!
replyContent: In the latest version, checked recurring tasks are automatically rescheduled at midnight. See Settings for other options. Thank you for your feedback.

content:
Great app that only asks for permissions it needs. In comparison to similar 
apps who request location, camera, microphone access and more, this one 
doesn't and that alone is greatly worth it's price. The app is well 
constructed and sophisticated, well beyond what I expected. I recommend 
this app to anyone looking for a great list program that won't invade your 
privacy.

A useful 'To do' list app allowing multiple category lists to be created. 
Various options for each list including creation of shopping lists that can 
be sustained and copied as needed to a 'Today' section without losing them 
after items are checked off. Backup and restore features also included. App 
provider was very responsive to a product improvement notified by email 
support. Looks like a very useful feature to add item costs to checklists.
